<div class="privacy-policy">
  <div class="light-grey-background">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row grey-container">
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="groupages-near white-inner-container">
      <div class="groupages-near-inner">
        <div class="container">
          <div>
            <span class="groupage"><b>Privacy Policy</b></span>
          </div>
          <div class="inner-container container-align">
            <p>Move Labs Lda. (“coshippers”, “us”, “we”, or “our”) operates <%= link_to 'https://www.coshippers.com', 'https://www.coshippers.com', style: "color: inherit;" %> (the “Site”). This section gives you information on our policies regarding the collection, use and sharing of Personal Information we receive from Users of the Site.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="inner-container container-align">
            <h3>Introduction</h3>
            <p>
              coshippers’s goal is to let you have find unused space in shared moves near you.
              Creating trust in our relationship is of utmost importance for coshippers, and one of the components is that we are fully committed to your privacy.
              We want you to know exactly what information we collect from you, how we collect it, what we do with it and how it is protected.
              Your personally identifiable information is never sold, rented or shared dishonestly.
              We use your Personal Information for providing you with a better experience and improving the Site.
              By using the Site, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="inner-container container-align">
            <h3>Information Collection And Use</h3>
            <p>
              While using our Site, we may ask you to provide us with certain personally identifiable information that can be used to contact or identify you.
              Personally identifiable information may include, but is not limited to, your name, your email address, your phone number, date of your move and your origin/destination addresses (“Personal Information”).
              We will keep a record of this information.
              Our online forms may require further information to help us understand your requirements, and find suitable suppliers for you.
              We may also monitor and/or record telephone & video calls for the purposes of quality control or requirements processing post-communication (like populating a detailed list of your household goods and calculate your overall volume for example).
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="inner-container container-align">
            <h3>Navigation Data</h3>
            <p>
              Like most websites, we collect data that your browser sends whenever you visit our Site (“Log Data”).
              This Data can include information such as your computer’s Internet Protocol (“IP”) address, the browser you are using and its version, the pages you visit on our Site, the date and time of your visit & the time you have spent on those pages and some other statistics.
              In addition, we may use third party services such as Google Analytics, Facebook Pixel or MixPanel that collect, monitor and analyze this.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="inner-container container-align">
            <h3>Cookies</h3>
            <p>
              Cookies are files with small amount of data, which may include an anonymous unique identifier.
              Cookies are sent to your browser from a web site and stored on your computer’s hard drive.
              Like many sites, we use “cookies” to collect information.
              You can instruct your browser to refuse all cookies or to indicate when a cookie is being sent.
              However, if you do not accept cookies, you may not be able to use some portions of our Site.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="inner-container container-align">
            <h3>How we use your information and how it could be shared</h3>
            <p>We do not share your personal information with companies, organizations or individuals outside of coshippers unless one of the following situations applies:</p>
            <p><i>To verify your requests</i></p>
            <p>In order to implement services that are offered on our website, coshippers may use your Personal Information to contact you by telephone, live video chat, SMS, email or post to confirm or verify the details of your requests.</p>
            <p><i>To request estimates and/or quotes on your behalf</i></p>
            <p>
              We may need to share your Personal Information with Partners you have selected on our website and/or while exchanging with coshippers, in order to perform any of the services you have instructed us to book on your behalf.
              In such situations, we may share your personal information needed for completion of the requested service.
            </p>
            <p><i>With your explicit consent</i></p>
            <p>We may share personal information that you have provided to coshippers to certain third parties, with your explicit consent (instruction from you, opt-in).</p>
            <p><i>Under legal circumstances</i></p>
            <p>If the transmission of your personal information is needed to meet any applicable law, legal process or governmental request, we may need to share it.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="inner-container container-align">
            <h3>Security</h3>
            <p>
              The security of your Personal Information is of utmost importance to us.
              That said, please be aware that no transmission method over the Internet is totally secure.
              This applies to electronic storage solutions too.
              While we strive to ensure your Personal Information is protected at all times, we cannot guarantee its definite security.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="inner-container container-align">
            <h3>Privacy Policy Changes</h3>
            <p>
              This Privacy Policy is effective as of 7 May 2018 and will remain in effect except with respect to any changes in its provisions in the future, which will be in effect immediately after being posted on this page.
              We reserve the right to update or change our Privacy Policy at any time. So please do check this Privacy Policy periodically.
              Your continued use of the Service after we post any modifications to the Privacy Policy on this page will constitute your acknowledgment of the modifications and your consent to abide and be bound by the modified Privacy Policy.
              Should any material change to this Policy occur, we will notify you either through your email address, or by placing a notice on our Site.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="inner-container container-align">
            <h3>Contact Us</h3>
            <p>If you have any questions about these Terms & Conditions, please contact us:</p>
            <%= render partial: 'contact_address' %>
            <p>or email us at help@coshippers.com</p>
          </div>
          <div class="inner-container container-align">
            <p>Last updated: 14 February 2019</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
